dow into his seminal thinking and makes us understand the contribution he made to Malaysian nation-building in the early years. Tawfik Ismail and Ooi Kee Beng deserve kudos for compiling these into one volume and for providing elaborate footnoting that presents the reader with an intriguing picture of the Cold War year of 1958. The book is a "must read" for the diplomatic corps and Malaysian foreign policy analysts.- Johan Saravanamuttu, Former political science Professor and Dean, Science University Malaysia (USM)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDiplomatszMalaysiavBiography. 0aDiplomats--Malaysia--Biography. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh1 aKee Beng, Ooi, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRithauddeen, Tengku Tan Sri Dato’ Seri Ahmad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106066830 cprintz978981230902040uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981230903740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789812309037423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789812309037/original  a978-3-11-060668-3  ISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  a978-3-11-066300-6  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102470-7  ISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aE